cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with modelling the delay in a wireless mesh network, which falls under the domain of networking. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper involves the analysis of packet generation and transmission, which is related to information theory. 
3. cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) - The paper deals with a network with multiple nodes, which can be modelled as a multi-agent system. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper involves modelling and analysis of a system (wireless mesh network) and its performance (delay), which falls under the domain of systems and control. 
5. cs.PF (Performance) - The paper deals with the performance analysis of a wireless mesh network, which falls under the domain of performance evaluation.
